<treatment id="03FF8560BE60FFE3FD29F9438EECFA7C" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03FF8560BE60FFE3FD29F9438EECFA7C" httpUri="http://treatment.plazi.org/id/03FF8560BE60FFE3FD29F9438EECFA7C" lastPageId="8" lastPageNumber="7" pageId="6" pageNumber="5">
<subSubSection id="C34C67FDBE60FFECFD29F94389A3F918" lastPageId="7" lastPageNumber="6" pageId="6" pageNumber="5" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph id="8BE93476BE60FFEDFD29F94389A3F97A" blockId="6.[716,1180,1678,1735]" box="[716,1180,1678,1702]" pageId="6" pageNumber="5">
<heading id="D0A1831ABE60FFEDFD29F94389A3F97A" box="[716,1180,1678,1702]" centered="true" fontSize="9" level="2" pageId="6" pageNumber="5" reason="2">
<taxonomicName id="4C564FF5BE60FFEDFD29F9438EB1F97A" authorityName=", Ponce-Saavedra and Sissom" authorityYear="2004" box="[716,910,1679,1702]" class="Arachnida" family="Vaejovidae" genus="Vaejovis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="6" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cisnerosi">
<emphasis id="B922E864BE60FFEDFD29F9438EB1F97A" box="[716,910,1679,1702]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="5">Vaejovis cisnerosi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is unlike all other spe-
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE93476BE60FFECFD29F96389A3F918" blockId="6.[716,1180,1678,1735]" lastBlockId="7.[716,1181,1245,1732]" lastPageId="7" lastPageNumber="6" pageId="6" pageNumber="5">
cies of 
<taxonomicName id="4C564FF5BE60FFEDFCF8F97C8EA9F91B" authority="in" authorityName="In" box="[797,918,1711,1735]" class="Arachnida" family="Vaejovidae" genus="Vaejovis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="6" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B922E864BE60FFEDFCF8F97C8E48F91B" box="[797,887,1712,1735]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="5">Vaejovis</emphasis>
in
</taxonomicName>
that the carinae of the dorsal and lateral surfaces of the metasoma are greatly reduced in strength (mostly obsolete) and completely smooth. In addition, the metasomal setation is highly reduced … giving it the lowest setal counts of any species in the genus. These features are autapomorphic.… The hemispermatophore of 
<taxonomicName id="4C564FF5BE61FFECFEB3FA098CF1FA00" authorityName=", Ponce-Saavedra and Sissom" authorityYear="2004" box="[342,462,1477,1500]" class="Arachnida" family="Vaejovidae" genus="Vaejovis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="7" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cisnerosi">
<emphasis id="B922E864BE61FFECFEB3FA098CF1FA00" box="[342,462,1477,1500]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="6">V. cisnerosi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is quite similar to those of the species of the 
<taxonomicName id="4C564FF5BE61FFECFDA3FA2A8C39F9C2" class="Arachnida" family="Vaejovidae" genus="Vaejovis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="7" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="eusthenura">
<emphasis id="B922E864BE61FFECFDA3FA2A8C39F9C2" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="6">V. eusthenura</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C564FF5BE61FFECFEFDF9CB8C95F9C2" authorityName=": Pocock" authorityYear="1902" box="[280,426,1542,1566]" class="Arachnida" family="Vaejovidae" genus="Vaejovis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="7" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="intrepidus">
<emphasis id="B922E864BE61FFECFEFDF9CB8C95F9C2" box="[280,426,1542,1566]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="6">V. intrepidus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C564FF5BE61FFECFE0EF9CB8DFCF9E3" class="Arachnida" family="Vaejovidae" genus="Vaejovis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="7" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="punctipalpi">
<emphasis id="B922E864BE61FFECFE0EF9CB8DFCF9E3" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="6">V. punctipalpi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species groups. There is a broad flange along the ental margin of the distal lamina [fused margin of dorsal and ventral troughs], and the ental process of the inner capsular lobe bears a series of hook- lets (Sissom, 1991) [spinose distal barb margin]. The position of trichobothria 
<emphasis id="B922E864BE61FFECFB6DFB3289A3FACA" box="[1160,1180,1278,1302]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="6">ib</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis id="B922E864BE61FFECFD1AFAEC8E30FAEB" box="[767,783,1312,1335]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="6">it</emphasis>
on the pedipalp chela fixed finger (displaced to near the 6th inner accessory denticle of the primary denticle row) and the possession of only five subrows of denticles on the chela fixed finger also suggest relationship with those groups. Finally, the ventromedian spinule row of the leg tarsi are flanked distally by two or more pairs of larger spinules, as in the aforementioned groups. The reduction of the carinae of the pedipalps and the absence of ventral carinae on the metasoma place the species closer to the 
<taxonomicName id="4C564FF5BE61FFECFC35F9608974F918" box="[976,1099,1708,1732]" class="Arachnida" family="Vaejovidae" genus="Vaejovis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="7" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="eusthenura">
<emphasis id="B922E864BE61FFECFC35F9608974F918" box="[976,1099,1708,1732]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="6">eusthenura</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<caption id="DF2964FEBE61FFECFF89FB928E9DFB73" pageId="7" pageNumber="6" startId="7.[108,194,1118,1139]" targetBox="[109,1209,232,1084]" targetPageId="7">
<paragraph id="8BE93476BE61FFECFF89FB928E9DFB73" blockId="7.[108,1212,1116,1199]" pageId="7" pageNumber="6">
FIGURE 4. Map of central Mexico, plotting known locality records for the vaejovid scorpion species, 
<taxonomicName id="4C564FF5BE61FFECFB81FB918F75FB4E" authority="Francke and Ponce-Saavedra, 2010" authorityName="Francke and Ponce-Saavedra" authorityYear="2010" class="Arachnida" family="Vaejovidae" genus="Kuarapu" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="7" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="purhepecha">
<emphasis id="B922E864BE61FFECFB81FB918DE1FB4E" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="6">Kuarapu purhepecha</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFC74987BE61FFECFF00FBB68F75FB4E" author="Francke, O. F. &amp; J. Ponce-Saavedra" box="[229,586,1146,1170]" pageId="7" pageNumber="6" pagination="51 - 57" refId="ref43435" refString="Francke, O. F., and J. Ponce-Saavedra. 2010. A new genus and species of scorpion (Scorpiones: Vaejovidae) from Michoacan, Mexico. Boletin de la Sociedad Entomologica Aragonesa 46: 51 - 57." type="journal article" year="2010">Francke and Ponce-Saavedra, 2010</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(square), 
<taxonomicName id="4C564FF5BE61FFECFD51FBB68921FB4E" authority="(Thorell, 1876)" baseAuthorityName="Thorell" baseAuthorityYear="1876" box="[692,1054,1146,1170]" class="Arachnida" family="Vaejovidae" genus="Thorellius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="7" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="intrepidus">
<emphasis id="B922E864BE61FFECFD51FBB68EBFFB4E" box="[692,896,1146,1170]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="6">Thorellius intrepidus</emphasis>
(Thorell, 1876)
</taxonomicName>
(triangles) and 
<taxonomicName id="4C564FF5BE61FFECFF8BFB5B8C15FB73" authorityName="Gonzalez-Santillan &amp; Prendini" authorityYear="2018" box="[110,298,1175,1199]" class="Arachnida" family="Vaejovidae" genus="Thorellius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="7" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="yuyuawi" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B922E864BE61FFECFF8BFB5B8C15FB73" box="[110,298,1175,1199]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="6">Thorellius yuyuawi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A211551FBE61FFECFED3FB5B8CBBFB72" box="[310,388,1175,1198]" pageId="7" pageNumber="6" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
(circle), based on data collected in the present study.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<subSubSection id="C34C67FDBE6EFFE3FF69FF2E8EECFA7C" pageId="8" pageNumber="7" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BE93476BE6EFFE3FF69FF2E8F63FE3E" blockId="8.[140,604,226,482]" pageId="8" pageNumber="7">
(e.g., in southern 
<collectingCountry id="F34174E6BE6EFFE3FE94FF2E8CF8FF26" box="[369,455,226,250]" name="Mexico" pageId="8" pageNumber="7">Mexico</collectingCountry>
, this would include 
<taxonomicName id="4C564FF5BE6EFFE3FF0FFECF8F63FEC7" authority="Karsch, 1879" authorityName="Karsch" authorityYear="1879" box="[234,604,259,283]" class="Arachnida" family="Vaejovidae" genus="Vaejovis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="8" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="punctatus">
<emphasis id="B922E864BE6EFFE3FF0FFECF8C82FEC6" box="[234,445,259,282]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="7">Vaejovis punctatus</emphasis>
Karsch, 1879
</taxonomicName>
[currently 
<taxonomicName id="4C564FF5BE6EFFE3FF1AFEE88DF1FE81" authority="(Karsch, 1879)" baseAuthorityName="Karsch" baseAuthorityYear="1879" class="Arachnida" family="Vaejovidae" genus="Mesomexovis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="8" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="punctatus">
<emphasis id="B922E864BE6EFFE3FF1AFEE88CC3FEE7" box="[255,508,292,315]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="7">Mesomexovis punctatus</emphasis>
(Karsch, 1879)
</taxonomicName>
] and its relatives); on the other hand, the reduction of the metasomal setation and the dorsoventral compression of the metasoma are similar to the conditions seen in the 
<taxonomicName id="4C564FF5BE6EFFE3FEA8FE058C86FE3D" baseAuthorityName="Thorell" baseAuthorityYear="1876" box="[333,441,457,481]" class="Arachnida" family="Vaejovidae" genus="Thorellius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="8" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="intrepidus">
<emphasis id="B922E864BE6EFFE3FEA8FE058C86FE3D" box="[333,441,457,481]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="7">intrepidus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species group.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE93476BE6EFFE3FF69FDCF8DE0FD1C" blockId="8.[108,636,515,704]" pageId="8" pageNumber="7">
<bibRefCitation id="EFC74987BE6EFFE3FF69FDCF8C8EFDC7" author="Soleglad, M. E. &amp; V. Fet" box="[140,433,515,539]" pageId="8" pageNumber="7" pagination="1 - 115" refId="ref45210" refString="Soleglad, M. E., and V. Fet. 2008. Contributions to Scorpion Systematics. III. Subfamilies Smeringurinae and Syntropinae (Scorpiones: Vaejovidae). Euscorpius 71: 1 - 115." type="journal article" year="2008">Soleglad and Fet (2008: 95)</bibRefCitation>
justified the transfer of 
<taxonomicName id="4C564FF5BE6EFFE3FF49FDE88C1DFDE7" authorityName=", Ponce-Saavedra and Sissom" authorityYear="2004" box="[172,290,548,571]" class="Arachnida" family="Vaejovidae" genus="Vaejovis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="8" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cisnerosi">
<emphasis id="B922E864BE6EFFE3FF49FDE88C1DFDE7" box="[172,290,548,571]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="7">V. cisnerosi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to 
<taxonomicName id="4C564FF5BE6EFFE3FEA0FDE88C92FDE0" authorityName=", Soleglad and Fet" authorityYear="2008" box="[325,429,548,572]" class="Arachnida" family="Vaejovidae" genus="Thorellius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="8" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B922E864BE6EFFE3FEA0FDE88C92FDE0" box="[325,429,548,572]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="7">Thorellius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, despite the uncertainty regarding its phylogenetic placement (
<bibRefCitation id="EFC74987BE6EFFE3FF96FDAA8CD8FDA2" author="Ponce-Saavedra, J. &amp; W. D. Sissom" box="[115,487,614,638]" pageId="8" pageNumber="7" pagination="539 - 544" refId="ref44440" refString="Ponce-Saavedra, J., and W. D. Sissom. 2004. A new species of the genus Vaejovis (Scorpiones, Vaejovidae) endemic to the Balsas basin of Michoacan, Mexico. Journal of Arachnology 32: 539 - 544." type="journal article" year="2004">Ponce-Saavedra and Sissom, 2004</bibRefCitation>
), and without testing that placement in a quantitative analysis, as follows:
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE93476BE6EFFE3FF69FD2D8CDCF9EF" blockId="8.[140,604,737,1588]" pageId="8" pageNumber="7">
Clearly the hemispermatophore, with its well developed lamellar hook [fused margin of dorsal and ventral troughs], the mating plug with its toothed barb [spinose distal barb margin], and the multiple pairs of ventral distal spinules of the leg tarsus imply this species is a member of tribe 
<taxonomicName id="4C564FF5BE6EFFE3FF2AFC048C75FC3C" authorityName="Kraepelin" authorityYear="1905" box="[207,330,968,992]" class="Arachnida" family="Vaejovidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="8" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Syntropini">Syntropini</taxonomicName>
. The chelal and metasomal carination of this species is unique… where the former exhibits vestigial to smooth carinae and the ventral carinae of the latter are obsolete. The existence of carinae on the chelae, though smooth, and the somewhat robust chelae imply this species is a member of subtribe 
<taxonomicName id="4C564FF5BE6EFFE3FF69FB1D8C34FB35" authorityName="Soleglad and Fet" authorityYear="2008" box="[140,267,1233,1257]" class="Arachnida" family="Vaejovidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="8" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subTribe" subTribe="Thorelliina">Thorelliina</taxonomicName>
. The carapace in 
<taxonomicName id="4C564FF5BE6EFFE3FE38FB1E8F63FB35" authorityName=", Ponce-Saavedra and Sissom" authorityYear="2004" box="[477,604,1234,1257]" class="Arachnida" family="Vaejovidae" genus="Vaejovis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="8" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cisnerosi">
<emphasis id="B922E864BE6EFFE3FE38FB1E8F63FB35" box="[477,604,1234,1257]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="7">T. cisnerosi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
lacks the anterior emargination extending to the lateral ocelli as seen in 
<taxonomicName id="4C564FF5BE6EFFE3FE33FADF8F13FAF7" authorityName="Soleglad and Fet" authorityYear="2008" box="[470,556,1299,1323]" class="Arachnida" family="Vaejovidae" genus="Kochius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="8" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B922E864BE6EFFE3FE33FADF8F13FAF7" box="[470,556,1299,1323]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="7">Kochius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and the placement of chelal trichobothrium 
<emphasis id="B922E864BE6EFFE3FF69FA9A8D97FAB1" box="[140,168,1366,1389]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="7">Dt</emphasis>
is well distal of the palm midpoint, indications of genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C564FF5BE6EFFE3FE65FABA8CD3FA52" authorityName=", Soleglad and Fet" authorityYear="2008" box="[384,492,1398,1422]" class="Arachnida" family="Vaejovidae" genus="Thorellius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="8" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B922E864BE6EFFE3FE65FABA8CD3FA52" box="[384,492,1398,1422]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="7">Thorellius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
... Finally, of somewhat less importance, the large size of this species, its large pectinal tooth count (20–22 for males and 20–21 for females), and its geographical distribution also indicates genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C564FF5BE6EFFE3FE91F9D08CE2F9E8" authorityName=", Soleglad and Fet" authorityYear="2008" box="[372,477,1564,1588]" class="Arachnida" family="Vaejovidae" genus="Thorellius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="8" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B922E864BE6EFFE3FE91F9D08CE2F9E8" box="[372,477,1564,1588]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="7">Thorellius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE93476BE6EFFE3FF69F9828EEBFCF0" blockId="8.[108,636,1613,1736]" lastBlockId="8.[684,1217,226,1440]" pageId="8" pageNumber="7">
As discussed by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC74987BE6EFFE3FEDAF9818DDAF95B" author="Gonzalez-Santillan, E. &amp; L. Prendini" pageId="8" pageNumber="7" pagination="1 - 71" refId="ref43523" refString="Gonzalez-Santillan, E., and L. Prendini. 2013. Redefinition and generic revision of the North American vaejovid scorpion subfamily Syntropinae Kraepelin, 1905, with descriptions of six new genera. Bulletin of the American Museum of Natural History 382: 1 - 71." type="journal article" year="2013">González-Santillán and Prendini (2013)</bibRefCitation>
, most of the new taxa proposed in the classification presented by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC74987BE6EFFE3FE61F9438F43F974" author="Soleglad, M. E. &amp; V. Fet" box="[388,636,1679,1704]" pageId="8" pageNumber="7" pagination="1 - 115" refId="ref45210" refString="Soleglad, M. E., and V. Fet. 2008. Contributions to Scorpion Systematics. III. Subfamilies Smeringurinae and Syntropinae (Scorpiones: Vaejovidae). Euscorpius 71: 1 - 115." type="journal article" year="2008">Soleglad and Fet (2008)</bibRefCitation>
were demonstrably paraphyletic or polyphyletic when tested by a quantitative phylogenetic analysis based on morphological characters and DNA sequences from the nuclear and mitochondrial genomes (
<bibRefCitation id="EFC74987BE6EFFE3FCCFFE898FCFFEA2" author="Gonzalez-Santillan, E. &amp; L. Prendini" pageId="8" pageNumber="7" pagination="341 - 405" refId="ref43572" refString="Gonzalez-Santillan, E., and L. Prendini. 2015 a. Phylogeny of the North American vaejovid subfamily Syntropinae Kraepelin, 1905, based on morphology, mitochondrial and nuclear DNA. Cladistics 31: 341 - 405." type="journal article" year="2015">González-Santillán and Prendini, 2015a</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName id="4C564FF5BE6EFFE3FCE7FEAA8E57FEA2" authorityName=", Soleglad and Fet" authorityYear="2008" box="[770,872,358,382]" class="Arachnida" family="Vaejovidae" genus="Thorellius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="8" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B922E864BE6EFFE3FCE7FEAA8E57FEA2" box="[770,872,358,382]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="7">Thorellius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, as defined by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC74987BE6EFFE3FBEFFEAA8FC8FE43" author="Soleglad, M. E. &amp; V. Fet" pageId="8" pageNumber="7" pagination="1 - 115" refId="ref45210" refString="Soleglad, M. E., and V. Fet. 2008. Contributions to Scorpion Systematics. III. Subfamilies Smeringurinae and Syntropinae (Scorpiones: Vaejovidae). Euscorpius 71: 1 - 115." type="journal article" year="2008">Soleglad and Fet (2008)</bibRefCitation>
, was consistently polyphyletic, and the group comprising 
<taxonomicName id="4C564FF5BE6EFFE3FC93FE658EF9FE1C" baseAuthorityName="Hoffmann" baseAuthorityYear="1931" box="[886,966,425,448]" class="Arachnida" family="Vaejovidae" genus="Thorellius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="8" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="atrox">
<emphasis id="B922E864BE6EFFE3FC93FE658EF9FE1C" box="[886,966,425,448]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="7">T. atrox</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C564FF5BE6EFFE3FC31FE658956FE1C" authorityName="Pocock" authorityYear="1898" box="[980,1129,425,448]" class="Arachnida" family="Vaejovidae" genus="Vaejovis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="8" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cristimanus">
<emphasis id="B922E864BE6EFFE3FC31FE658956FE1C" box="[980,1129,425,448]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="7">T. cristimanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="4C564FF5BE6EFFE3FB4FFE658E29FE3D" baseAuthorityName="Thorell" baseAuthorityYear="1876" class="Arachnida" family="Vaejovidae" genus="Thorellius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="8" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="intrepidus">
<emphasis id="B922E864BE6EFFE3FB4FFE658E29FE3D" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="7">T. intrepidus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
consistently monophyletic. In consequence, 
<taxonomicName id="4C564FF5BE6EFFE3FCE3FE268E53FDDE" authorityName=", Soleglad and Fet" authorityYear="2008" box="[774,876,490,514]" class="Arachnida" family="Vaejovidae" genus="Thorellius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="8" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B922E864BE6EFFE3FCE3FE268E53FDDE" box="[774,876,490,514]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="7">Thorellius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was restricted to these species, and the other species transferred to different genera by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC74987BE6EFFE3FD19FDE08986FD98" author="Gonzalez-Santillan, E. &amp; L. Prendini" box="[764,1209,556,580]" pageId="8" pageNumber="7" pagination="1 - 71" refId="ref43523" refString="Gonzalez-Santillan, E., and L. Prendini. 2013. Redefinition and generic revision of the North American vaejovid scorpion subfamily Syntropinae Kraepelin, 1905, with descriptions of six new genera. Bulletin of the American Museum of Natural History 382: 1 - 71." type="journal article" year="2013">González-Santillán and Prendini (2013)</bibRefCitation>
. 
<taxonomicName id="4C564FF5BE6EFFE3FD49FD818E2CFDB9" authorityName="Gonzalez-Santillan and Prendini" authorityYear="2013" box="[684,787,589,613]" class="Arachnida" family="Vaejovidae" genus="Balsateres" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="8" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B922E864BE6EFFE3FD49FD818E2CFDB9" box="[684,787,589,613]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="7">Balsateres</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was created to account for the phylogenetic position and unique diagnostic character combination of 
<taxonomicName id="4C564FF5BE6EFFE3FCBEFD5C8EEEFD7B" authorityName=", Ponce-Saavedra and Sissom" authorityYear="2004" box="[859,977,656,679]" class="Arachnida" family="Vaejovidae" genus="Vaejovis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="8" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cisnerosi">
<emphasis id="B922E864BE6EFFE3FCBEFD5C8EEEFD7B" box="[859,977,656,679]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="7">V. cisnerosi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, creating 
<taxonomicName id="4C564FF5BE6EFFE3FBDAFD5C8989FD7B" authorityName=", Ponce-Saavedra and Sissom" authorityYear="2004" box="[1087,1206,656,679]" class="Arachnida" family="Vaejovidae" genus="Vaejovis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="8" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cisnerosi">
<emphasis id="B922E864BE6EFFE3FBDAFD5C8989FD7B" box="[1087,1206,656,679]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="7">B. cisnerosi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, whereas 
<taxonomicName id="4C564FF5BE6EFFE3FCE8FD7D8E98FD14" box="[781,935,688,712]" class="Arachnida" family="Vaejovidae" genus="Vaejovis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="8" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="occidentalis">
<emphasis id="B922E864BE6EFFE3FCE8FD7D8E98FD14" box="[781,935,688,712]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="7">V. occidentalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C564FF5BE6EFFE3FC06FD7D8940FD14" authorityName="Pocock" authorityYear="1902" box="[995,1151,688,712]" class="Arachnida" family="Vaejovidae" genus="Vaejovis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="8" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="subcristatus">
<emphasis id="B922E864BE6EFFE3FC06FD7D8940FD14" box="[995,1151,688,712]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="7">V. subcristatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
were transferred to 
<taxonomicName id="4C564FF5BE6EFFE3FCA4FD1E8EF3FD35" authorityName="Gonzalez-Santillan &amp; Prendini" authorityYear="2013" box="[833,972,722,745]" class="Arachnida" family="Vaejovidae" genus="Mesomexovis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="8" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B922E864BE6EFFE3FCA4FD1E8EF3FD35" box="[833,972,722,745]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="7">Mesomexovis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, creating 
<taxonomicName id="4C564FF5BE6EFFE3FBD4FD1E8ECAFCD7" authority="(Hoffmann, 1931)" baseAuthorityName="Hoffmann" baseAuthorityYear="1931" class="Arachnida" family="Vaejovidae" genus="Mesomexovis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="8" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="occidentalis">
<emphasis id="B922E864BE6EFFE3FBD4FD1E8E19FCD7" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="7">Mesomexovis occidentalis</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFC74987BE6EFFE3FCD3FD3F8ED3FCD7" author="Hoffmann, C. C." box="[822,1004,755,779]" pageId="8" pageNumber="7" pagination="291 - 408" refId="ref43782" refString="Hoffmann, C. C. 1931. Monografias para la entomologia medica de Mexico. Monografia 2, Los escorpiones de Mexico. Primera parte: Diplocentridae, Chactidae, Vejovidae. Anales del Instituto de Biologia Universidad Nacional Autonoma de Mexico 2: 291 - 408." type="journal article" year="1931">Hoffmann, 1931</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C564FF5BE6EFFE3FBCAFD3F8EEEFCF0" authority="(Pocock, 1902)" baseAuthorityName="Pocock" baseAuthorityYear="1902" class="Arachnida" family="Vaejovidae" genus="Mesomexovis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="8" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="subcristatus">
<emphasis id="B922E864BE6EFFE3FBCAFD3F8E18FCF0" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="7">Mesomexovis subcristatus</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFC74987BE6EFFE3FCD0FCD88EF6FCF0" author="Pocock, R. I." box="[821,969,788,812]" pageId="8" pageNumber="7" refId="ref44309" refString="Pocock, R. I. 1902. Arachnida, Scorpiones, Pedipalpi and Solifugae. Biologia Centrali-Americana. London: Taylor and Francis, 71 pp." type="book" year="1902">Pocock, 1902</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE93476BE6EFFE3FD29FCF98EECFA7C" blockId="8.[684,1217,226,1440]" pageId="8" pageNumber="7">
<bibRefCitation id="EFC74987BE6EFFE3FD29FCF98971FC91" author="Francke, O. F. &amp; J. Ponce-Saavedra" box="[716,1102,821,845]" pageId="8" pageNumber="7" pagination="51 - 57" refId="ref43435" refString="Francke, O. F., and J. Ponce-Saavedra. 2010. A new genus and species of scorpion (Scorpiones: Vaejovidae) from Michoacan, Mexico. Boletin de la Sociedad Entomologica Aragonesa 46: 51 - 57." type="journal article" year="2010">Francke and Ponce-Saavedra (2010)</bibRefCitation>
discussed the placement of 
<taxonomicName id="4C564FF5BE6EFFE3FC67FC9B8EDDFCB2" box="[898,994,855,878]" class="Arachnida" family="Vaejovidae" genus="Kuarapu" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="8" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B922E864BE6EFFE3FC67FC9B8EDDFCB2" box="[898,994,855,878]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="7">Kuarapu</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the context of 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC74987BE6EFFE3FD49FCBB8EE2FC53" author="Soleglad, M. E. &amp; V. Fet" box="[684,989,887,911]" pageId="8" pageNumber="7" pagination="1 - 115" refId="ref45210" refString="Soleglad, M. E., and V. Fet. 2008. Contributions to Scorpion Systematics. III. Subfamilies Smeringurinae and Syntropinae (Scorpiones: Vaejovidae). Euscorpius 71: 1 - 115." type="journal article" year="2008">Soleglad and Fet’s (2008)</bibRefCitation>
classification, and offered two alternatives: placement within 
<taxonomicName id="4C564FF5BE6EFFE3FB6FFC548FC6FC0D" authorityName="Kraepelin" authorityYear="1905" class="Arachnida" family="Vaejovidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="8" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Syntropini">Syntropini</taxonomicName>
, based on the spinose distal barb margin of the hemimating plug of the male hemispermatophore, peg sensillae on the basal pectinal teeth of the female, and five ventral spinules on the telotarsus of leg III; or within 
<taxonomicName id="4C564FF5BE6EFFE3FBA0FBF18E9AFBAB" authority="Soleglad and Fet, 2008" authorityName="Soleglad and Fet" authorityYear="2008" class="Arachnida" family="Vaejovidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="8" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Stahnkeini">
Stahnkeini 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC74987BE6EFFE3FD49FB928E9AFBAB" author="Soleglad, M. E. &amp; V. Fet" box="[684,933,1118,1143]" pageId="8" pageNumber="7" pagination="1 - 115" refId="ref45210" refString="Soleglad, M. E., and V. Fet. 2008. Contributions to Scorpion Systematics. III. Subfamilies Smeringurinae and Syntropinae (Scorpiones: Vaejovidae). Euscorpius 71: 1 - 115." type="journal article" year="2008">Soleglad and Fet, 2008</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, based on the shared serrate cutting edge of the pedipalp chela fingers and the medial position of trichobothria 
<emphasis id="B922E864BE6EFFE3FB93FB6C89B5FB64" box="[1142,1162,1184,1208]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="7">ib</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis id="B922E864BE6EFFE3FD49FB0E8F84FB05" box="[684,699,1218,1241]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="7">it</emphasis>
on the pedipalp chela fixed finger. The analyses of 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC74987BE6EFFE3FD2DFB2F89BAFB27" author="Gonzalez-Santillan, E. &amp; L. Prendini" box="[712,1157,1251,1275]" pageId="8" pageNumber="7" pagination="341 - 405" refId="ref43572" refString="Gonzalez-Santillan, E., and L. Prendini. 2015 a. Phylogeny of the North American vaejovid subfamily Syntropinae Kraepelin, 1905, based on morphology, mitochondrial and nuclear DNA. Cladistics 31: 341 - 405." type="journal article" year="2015">González-Santillán and Prendini (2015a)</bibRefCitation>
confirmed the first hypothesis, based on the spinose distal barb margin of the hemimating plug, uniquely synapomorphic for 
<taxonomicName id="4C564FF5BE6EFFE3FC19FA8A89BCFA82" authorityName="Kraepelin" authorityYear="1905" box="[1020,1155,1350,1374]" class="Arachnida" family="Vaejovidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="8" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Syntropinae">Syntropinae</taxonomicName>
, and consistently recovered 
<taxonomicName id="4C564FF5BE6EFFE3FC59FAA48922FAA3" box="[956,1053,1384,1407]" class="Arachnida" family="Vaejovidae" genus="Kuarapu" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="8" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B922E864BE6EFFE3FC59FAA48922FAA3" box="[956,1053,1384,1407]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="7">Kuarapu</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as the basal member the 
<taxonomicName id="4C564FF5BE6EFFE3FCDFFA448EB0FA7C" authorityName="Soleglad and Fet" authorityYear="2008" box="[826,911,1416,1440]" class="Arachnida" family="Vaejovidae" genus="Kochius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="8" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B922E864BE6EFFE3FCDFFA448EB0FA7C" box="[826,911,1416,1440]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="7">Kochius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
clade.
</paragraph>
